      "Text": "An update for OpenEXR is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP1.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "OpenEXR is a high dynamic-range (HDR) image file format originally developed by Industrial Light \u0026 Magic for use in computer imaging applications.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nAn issue in Academy Software Foundation openexr v.3.2.3 and before allows a local attacker to cause a denial of service (DoS) via the convert function of exrmultipart.cpp.(CVE-2024-31047)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for OpenEXR is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP1.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
